objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: To assess the progression-free survival (PFS) of veliparib in combination with carboplatin (C) and paclitaxel (P) compared to placebo with C/P in subjects with a BRCA1 and/or BRCA2 Mutation and HER2-Negative Metastatic or Locally Advanced Unresectable Breast Cancer.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Overall Survival
objectives.text: To assess overall survival (OS) in subjects treated with veliparib in combination with C/P versus subjects treated with placebo with C/P.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Clinical Benefit Rate
objectives.text: To assess clinical benefit rate (CBR) in subjects treated with veliparib in combination with C/P versus subjects treated with placebo with C/P.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Objective Response Rate
objectives.text: To assess objective response rate (ORR) in subjects treated with veliparib in combination with C/P versus subjects treated with placebo with C/P.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - PFS2
objectives.text: To assess PFS2 in subjects treated with veliparib in combination with C/P versus subjects treated with placebo with C/P.

objectives.name: Tertiary Objective - Duration of Overall Response
objectives.text: To assess duration of overall response (DOR).

objectives.name: Tertiary Objective - ECOG Performance Status
objectives.text: To assess change in ECOG performance status.

objectives.name: Tertiary Objective - Quality of Life
objectives.text: To assess change in Quality of Life (QoL).

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy and tolerability of veliparib in combination with C/P compared to placebo plus C/P.

endpoints.name: Progression-free Survival (PFS)
endpoints.text: The number of days from the date the subject is randomized to the date the subject experiences disease progression, or to the date of death (all causes of mortality) if disease progression is not reached.

endpoints.name: Overall Survival (OS)
endpoints.text: The number of days from the day the subject is randomized to the date of the subject's death.

endpoints.name: Clinical Benefit Rate (CBR)
endpoints.text: The progression-free rate at 24 weeks from the Kaplan-Meier curve for time to progression (defined as from the date of randomization to the date of disease progression).

endpoints.name: Objective Response Rate (ORR)
endpoints.text: The proportion of subjects with a complete or partial objective response based on RECIST (version 1.1).

endpoints.name: PFS2
endpoints.text: The number of days from the day the subject is randomized to the date that the subject has disease progression or death of any cause on the subsequent therapy, whichever occurs first.

endpoints.name: Duration of Overall Response (DOR)
endpoints.text: Duration of overall response (DOR) evaluated according to progression per RECIST (version 1.1).

endpoints.name: Quality of Life (QoL)
endpoints.text: Change in Quality of Life (QoL) via the EORTC QLQ-C30/BR23 and EQ-5D-5L questionnaires.

endpoints.name: Safety and Tolerability
endpoints.text: Study drug exposure, adverse events, serious adverse events, all deaths, as well as changes in laboratory determinations and vital sign parameters.

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand (PFS)
estimands.populationSummary: Men and women ≥ 18 years with HER2-negative metastatic or locally advanced unresectable breast cancer and BRCA1/2 germline mutation (ITT population with documented mutations) Summary measure: Hazard Ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Discontinuation of study treatment for reasons other than progression
intercurrentEvents.text: Subjects who discontinue therapy without progressive disease

intercurrentEvents.name: Initiation of subsequent anti-cancer therapy
intercurrentEvents.text: Subjects who initiate another anti-cancer therapy prior to documented progression

estimands.treatment: Veliparib (120 mg BID Days -2 to 5) + Carboplatin (AUC 6) + Paclitaxel (80 mg/m2) vs Placebo + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel
estimands.analysisPopulation: Men and women ≥ 18 years with HER2-negative metastatic or locally advanced unresectable breast cancer and BRCA1/2 germline mutation (ITT population with documented mutations)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Progression-free survival (PFS) defined as days from randomization to disease progression (RECIST 1.1) or death

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand (OS)
estimands.populationSummary: Men and women ≥ 18 years with HER2-negative metastatic or locally advanced unresectable breast cancer and BRCA1/2 germline mutation Summary measure: Hazard Ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment Crossover
intercurrentEvents.text: Subjects randomized to placebo crossing over to unblinded veliparib monotherapy after documented progression

estimands.treatment: Veliparib + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel vs Placebo + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel
estimands.analysisPopulation: Men and women ≥ 18 years with HER2-negative metastatic or locally advanced unresectable breast cancer and BRCA1/2 germline mutation
estimands.variableOfInterest: Overall Survival (OS) defined as days from randomization to death from any cause

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand (ORR)
estimands.populationSummary: Subjects with at least one measurable lesion at baseline and documented BRCA mutation Summary measure: Odds Ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Death prior to tumor assessment
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject dies before first post-baseline scan

estimands.treatment: Veliparib + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel vs Placebo + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel
estimands.analysisPopulation: Subjects with at least one measurable lesion at baseline and documented BRCA mutation
estimands.variableOfInterest: Objective Response Rate (ORR) based on RECIST 1.1

estimands.name: Safety Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Randomized subjects who received at least one dose of study drug (Safety Population) Summary measure: Risk Difference.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment Discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of study drug due to toxicity

estimands.treatment: Veliparib + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel vs Placebo + Carboplatin + Paclitaxel
estimands.analysisPopulation: Randomized subjects who received at least one dose of study drug (Safety Population)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Incidence of adverse events, serious adverse events, and changes in laboratory parameters
